gs":[{"name":"Hatch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Hatch (Bedfordshire, Devon, Hampshire, Somerset, Wiltshire), Hacche in South Molton (Devon), or else a topographic name from residence near a hatch, a gate leading to a forest or sometimes a sluice-gate, from Middle English <i>hacche</i> ‘gate’ (Old English <i>hæcce</i>, Kentish Old English <i>hec(c)</i>). This name has been in Ireland since the 17th century, associated with County Meath and the nearby part of Louth."],"variants":[{"name":"Hedge","meanings":["English: topographic name for someone who lived by a hedge or enclosure, from Middle English <i>hegge</i> ‘hedge, fence’. In the early Middle Ages, hedges were not merely dividers between fields, but had an important defensive function when planted around a settlement or enclosure.","English: probably also a variant of   Hatch  , with voicing of the final consonant.","Americanized form (translation into English) of German   Hecke  ."]},{"name":"Hatcher","meanings":["English (southern): topographic name for someone who lived by a gate, from Middle English <i>haccher(e)</i>, a derivative of <i>hacche</i> ‘gate’. This normally denoted a gate marking the entrance to a forest or other enclosed piece of land, sometimes a floodgate or sluice-gate. Compare   Hatch  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Hatch was born in 1300, in Woodleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom as the son of John Hatch. He had at least 1 son with Joane Worlington."},"et":{"       1300–":"1300–Surnud","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1302–Male":"1302–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1280–Male":"1280–Surnud","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","       1300":"1300","1280":"1280","Woodleigh,Devon,Eng":"Woodleigh, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"       1300–":"1300–Kuollut","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1302–Male":"1302–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1280–Male":"1280–Kuollut","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","       1300":"1300","1280":"1280","Woodleigh,Devon,Eng":"Woodleigh, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"       1300–":"1300–Décédé","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1302–Male":"1302–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1280–Male":"1280–Décédé","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","       1300":"1300","1280":"1280","Woodleigh,Devon,Eng":"Woodleigh, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Hatch est né en 1300, à Woodleigh, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de John Hatch. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Joane Worlington."},"de":{"       1300–":"1300–Verstorben","1300–Male":"1300–Verstorben","1302–Male":"1302–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1280–Male":"1280–Verstorben","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","       1300":"1300","1280":"1280","Woodleigh,Devon,Eng":"Woodleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"William Hatch wurde 1300 in Woodleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom, als Sohn von John Hatch geboren. Er hatte mit Joane Worlington mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"       1300–":"1300–Desede","1300–Male":"1300–Desede","1302–Male":"1302–Desede","–Female":"Desede","–Male":"Desede","1280–Male":"1280–Desede","1302":"1302","1300":"1300",